The size of the synthesised NQDs and NQD-GNPs was analysed by TEM (Fig. 5
                        ). The size of the NQDs was less than 10 nm (Fig. 5i). At the same time, NQD-GNP demonstrated a size of 25.30 ± 6.68 nm without any aggregation. The FTIR spectra were analysed to study the peaks corresponding to various functional groups. The FTIR spectra of NQD exhibit a peak at 1637.56 cm−1 corresponding to stretching vibration of CC, which is not present in the FTIR spectra of gelatin but it is present in the NQD-GNPs (Fig. 6
                        A). XRD analysis of NQD-GNP demonstrated the 2Ɵ angle at 22° (Fig. 6B).
